 <span data-ttu-id="5b176-304">Redirigé <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> flux peut être lu de façon synchrone ou asynchrone.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5b176-304">The redirected <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> stream can be read synchronously or asynchronously.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5b176-305">Méthodes telles que <xref:System.IO.StreamReader.Read%2A>, <xref:System.IO.StreamReader.ReadLine%2A>, et <xref:System.IO.StreamReader.ReadToEnd%2A> effectuer des opérations de lecture synchrones sur le flux de sortie du processus.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5b176-305">Methods such as <xref:System.IO.StreamReader.Read%2A>, <xref:System.IO.StreamReader.ReadLine%2A>, and <xref:System.IO.StreamReader.ReadToEnd%2A> perform synchronous read operations on the output stream of the process.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5b176-306">Ces synchrone lire les opérations ne se terminent pas jusqu'à ce qu’associé <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process> écrit dans son <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> diffuser en continu ou ferme le flux.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5b176-306">These synchronous read operations do not complete until the associated <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process> writes to its <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> stream, or closes the stream.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="5b176-307">En revanche, <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.BeginOutputReadLine%2A> démarre asynchrone des opérations de lecture sur le <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> flux.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5b176-307">In contrast, <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.BeginOutputReadLine%2A> starts asynchronous read operations on the <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5b176-308">Cette méthode permet à un gestionnaire d’événements désigné (consultez <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.OutputDataReceived>) pour le flux de sortie et immédiatement retourne à l’appelant, qui peut effectuer d’autres tâches pendant que la sortie de flux est dirigée vers le Gestionnaire d’événements.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5b176-308">This method enables a designated event handler (see <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.OutputDataReceived>) for the stream output and immediately returns to the caller, which can perform other work while the stream output is directed to the event handler.</span></span>  
  
> [!NOTE]
>  <span data-ttu-id="5b176-309">L’application qui traite la sortie asynchrone doit appeler la <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.WaitForExit%2A> méthode pour vous assurer que le tampon de sortie a été vidé.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5b176-309">The application that is processing the asynchronous output should call the <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.WaitForExit%2A> method to ensure that the output buffer has been flushed.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="5b176-310">Synchrone lire opérations introduisent une dépendance entre l’appelant qui lit à partir de la <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> flux et l’enfant traitement l’écriture dans ce flux.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5b176-310">Synchronous read operations introduce a dependency between the caller reading from the <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> stream and the child process writing to that stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5b176-311">Ces dépendances peuvent entraîner des conditions d’interblocage.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5b176-311">These dependencies can cause deadlock conditions.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5b176-312">Lorsque l’appelant lit le flux redirigé d’un processus enfant, il est dépendant de l’enfant.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5b176-312">When the caller reads from the redirected stream of a child process, it is dependent on the child.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5b176-313">L’appelant attend l’opération de lecture jusqu'à ce que l’enfant écrit dans le flux ou ferme le flux.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5b176-313">The caller waits for the read operation until the child writes to the stream or closes the stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5b176-314">Lorsque le processus enfant écrit suffisamment de données pour remplir son flux redirigé, il est dépendant du parent.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5b176-314">When the child process writes enough data to fill its redirected stream, it is dependent on the parent.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5b176-315">Le processus enfant attend l’opération d’écriture suivante jusqu'à ce que le parent lit dans le flux complet ou ferme le flux.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5b176-315">The child process waits for the next write operation until the parent reads from the full stream or closes the stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5b176-316">La condition de blocage se produit lorsque l’appelant et le processus enfant attendent mutuellement effectuer une opération, et aucun ne puisse continuer.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5b176-316">The deadlock condition results when the caller and child process wait for each other to complete an operation, and neither can continue.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5b176-317">Vous pouvez éviter les interblocages en évaluant les dépendances entre l’appelant et le processus enfant.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5b176-317">You can avoid deadlocks by evaluating dependencies between the caller and child process.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="5b176-318">Par exemple, le code c# suivant montre comment lire un flux redirigé et attendre que le processus enfant s’arrête.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5b176-318">For example, the following C# code shows how to read from a redirected stream and wait for the child process to exit.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
Process p = new Process();  
p.StartInfo.UseShellExecute = false;  
p.StartInfo.RedirectStandardOutput = true;  
p.StartInfo.FileName = "Write500Lines.exe";  
p.Start();  
  
// To avoid deadlocks, always read the output stream first and then wait.  
string output = p.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd();  
p.WaitForExit();  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="5b176-319">L’exemple de code permet d’éviter une condition de blocage en appelant `p.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd` avant `p.WaitForExit`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5b176-319">The code example avoids a deadlock condition by calling `p.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd` before `p.WaitForExit`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5b176-320">Une condition de blocage peut se produire si le processus parent appelle `p.WaitForExit` avant `p.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd` et le processus enfant écrit suffisamment de texte pour remplir le flux redirigé.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5b176-320">A deadlock condition can result if the parent process calls `p.WaitForExit` before `p.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd` and the child process writes enough text to fill the redirected stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5b176-321">Le processus parent attendre indéfiniment que le processus enfant s’arrête.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5b176-321">The parent process would wait indefinitely for the child process to exit.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5b176-322">Le processus enfant attend indéfiniment que le parent lire à partir de la version complète <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> flux.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5b176-322">The child process would wait indefinitely for the parent to read from the full <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> stream.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="5b176-323">Il existe un problème similaire lorsque vous lisez tout le texte à partir de la sortie standard et le flux d’erreur standard.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5b176-323">There is a similar issue when you read all text from both the standard output and standard error streams.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5b176-324">Par exemple, le code c# suivant effectue une opération de lecture sur les deux flux.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5b176-324">For example, the following C# code performs a read operation on both streams.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
// To avoid deadlocks, use asynchronous read operations on at least one of the streams.  
// Do not perform a synchronous read to the end of both redirected streams.  
p.BeginOutputReadLine();  
string error = p.StandardError.ReadToEnd();  
p.WaitForExit();  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="5b176-325">L’exemple de code permet d’éviter la condition de blocage en effectuant asynchrone des opérations de lecture sur le <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> flux.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5b176-325">The code example avoids the deadlock condition by performing asynchronous read operations on the <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5b176-326">Un blocage survient si le processus parent appelle `p.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd` suivie `p.StandardError.ReadToEnd` et le processus enfant écrit suffisamment de texte pour remplir son flux d’erreurs.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5b176-326">A deadlock condition results if the parent process calls `p.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd` followed by `p.StandardError.ReadToEnd` and the child process writes enough text to fill its error stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5b176-327">Le processus parent attend indéfiniment que le processus enfant ferme son <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> flux.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5b176-327">The parent process would wait indefinitely for the child process to close its <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5b176-328">Le processus enfant attend indéfiniment que le parent lire à partir de la version complète <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardError%2A> flux.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5b176-328">The child process would wait indefinitely for the parent to read from the full <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardError%2A> stream.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="5b176-329">Vous pouvez utiliser des opérations de lecture asynchrones pour éviter ces dépendances et leur blocage potentiel.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5b176-329">You can use asynchronous read operations to avoid these dependencies and their deadlock potential.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5b176-330">Vous pouvez également éviter la condition de blocage en créant deux threads et en lisant la sortie de chaque flux sur un thread distinct.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5b176-330">Alternately, you can avoid the deadlock condition by creating two threads and reading the output of each stream on a separate thread.</span></span>  
  
   
  
